{{IPAfont|⟨imo<sub>(1)</sub> pi<sub>1</sub>to<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/imopitə/}} → {{IPAchar|/imofito/}} → {{IPAchar|/imowito/}} → *{{IPAchar|/imowuto/}} {{IPAchar|/imoːto/}}

Originally a compound of {{m|ja||妹|tr=imo|pos=close female companion}} + {{m|ja|人|tr=hito||[[person]]}}.<ref>{{R:Daijirin}}</ref><ref>{{R:Daijisen}}</ref>

The shift from {{IPAchar|/imofito/}} → {{IPAchar|/imoːto/}} is an instance of {{m|ja|:w:ja:ウ音便|ウ音便|tr=u onbin|''u'' sound shift}}, found in terms with bilabial consonants ({{IPAchar|/m/}}, {{IPAchar|/b/}}, {{IPAchar|/w/}}) followed by ''i''; commonly seen in terms such as {{m|ja|玄人|tr=kurōto||[[professional]]}}, {{m|ja|素人|tr=shirōto||[[amateur]]}}, or possibly, {{m|ja|相撲|tr=sumō||[[sumo]]}}.

